# XERO45 Sync Error: Invalid Authentication Token

If you see the error message **“XERO45 Sync Error: Unable to sync Xero data due to an invalid authentication token. Please disconnect and reconnect Xero in the workspace.”**, it means the authentication token connecting Expensify to Xero has expired or is no longer valid.

Until the connection is refreshed, syncing and exports will fail.

---

## Why the XERO45 Sync Error Happens

The XERO45 sync error occurs when:

- The Xero authentication token has expired  
- The Xero connection was revoked  
- The connected Xero account credentials changed  

When the token is invalid, Expensify cannot access Xero data.

---

## How to Fix the XERO45 Sync Error in New Expensify

### Step 1: Save Your Workspace Configuration (Recommended)

Before disconnecting:

1. Go to the **navigation tabs on the left** and select **Workspaces**.
2. Select your Workspace.
3. Select **Accounting**.

Take screenshots or note the settings under:

- **Export**
- **Coding**
- **Advanced**

Disconnecting may remove imported data and configuration.

---

### Step 2: Disconnect Xero

On web:

1. Go to **Workspaces > [Workspace Name] > Accounting**.
2. Click the **three-dot icon** to the right of the Xero connection.
3. Click **Disconnect from Xero**.
4. Click **Disconnect** again in the confirmation window.
5. Manually refresh the page to confirm the connection is fully removed.

On mobile:

1. Tap **Workspaces** from the navigation tabs on the bottom.
2. Select your Workspace.
3. Tap **Accounting**.
4. Tap the **three-dot icon** next to the Xero connection.
5. Tap **Disconnect** and confirm.

---

### Step 3: Reconnect to Xero

1. Click **Connect to Xero**.
2. Follow the steps in this guide:  
   [Connect to Xero (New Expensify)](https://help.expensify.com/articles/new-expensify/connections/xero/Connect-to-Xero)
3. Log in using the appropriate Xero admin credentials.
4. Complete the authorization flow.

---

### Step 4: Retry the Sync

After reconnecting:

1. Go to **Workspaces > [Workspace Name] > Accounting**.
2. Click the **three-dot icon**.
3. Click **Sync now**.
4. Retry exporting the report.

---

# FAQ

## Do I need Xero admin access to reconnect?

Yes. You must use a Xero account with admin permissions for the connected organization.

## Will disconnecting remove my configuration?

It may remove imported options and settings, which is why saving your configuration beforehand is recommended.
